  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Hoare\" title=\"House Hoare\"><img alt=\"House Hoare 2.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f7/House_Hoare_2.svg/50px-House_Hoare_2.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f7/House_Hoare_2.svg/75px-House_Hoare_2.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f7/House_Hoare_2.svg/100px-House_Hoare_2.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> King</span><br />Harrag Hoare</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Hoare\" title=\"House Hoare\"><img alt=\"House Hoare 2.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f7/House_Hoare_2.svg/50px-House_Hoare_2.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f7/House_Hoare_2.svg/75px-House_Hoare_2.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f7/House_Hoare_2.svg/100px-House_Hoare_2.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">Monarch</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/High_King_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"High King of the Iron Islands\">High King of the Iron Islands</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">Personal Information</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">Family</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Dynasty</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Hoare\" title=\"House Hoare\">House Hoare</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Ravos_Hoare\" title=\"Ravos Hoare\">Ravos Hoare</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">References</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Harrag Hoare</b> was a <a href=\"/index.php/High_King_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"High King of the Iron Islands\">High King of the Iron Islands</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Hoare\" title=\"House Hoare\">House Hoare</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Ravos_Hoare\" title=\"Ravos Hoare\">Ravos the Raper</a> was his son.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harrag_Hoare&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>According to <a href=\"/index.php/Aeron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Aeron Greyjoy\">Aeron Greyjoy</a>, Harrag was chosen by a <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsmoot\" title=\"Kingsmoot\">kingsmoot</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup> Unlike many kings of his time, Harrag's reign resembled those of the reavers of the <a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_Heroes\" title=\"Age of Heroes\">Age of Heroes</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_black_blood.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_black_blood.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the reign of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Stark\" title=\"Theon Stark\">Theon Stark</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/King_in_the_North\" title=\"King in the North\">King of Winter</a> known as the Hungry Wolf, Harrag led a fleet of longships from <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Wyk\" title=\"Great Wyk\">Great Wyk</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Wyk\" title=\"Old Wyk\">Old Wyk</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Pyke_(island)\" title=\"Pyke (island)\">Pyke</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Orkmont\" title=\"Orkmont\">Orkmont</a> against the western coast of the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a>. Harrag conquered the <a href=\"/index.php/Stony_Shore\" title=\"Stony Shore\">Stony Shore</a> and burned swathes of the <a href=\"/index.php/Wolfswood\" title=\"Wolfswood\">wolfswood</a>, while <a href=\"/index.php/Bear_Island\" title=\"Bear Island\">Bear Island</a> became a base for reaving for Harrag's son, <a href=\"/index.php/Ravos_Hoare\" title=\"Ravos Hoare\">Ravos the Raper</a>. Theon slew Ravos with his own hand, however, and expelled the ironmen from his shores.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Although Harrag's invasion was repulsed, the ironborn would return during the reign of Harrag's grandson, King <a href=\"/index.php/Erich_Hoare\" title=\"Erich Hoare\">Erich the Eagle</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harrag_Hoare&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Harrag Hoare was a contemporary of Theon Stark, during the <a href=\"/index.php/Coming_of_the_Andals\" title=\"Coming of the Andals\">coming of the Andals</a>, twice stated in <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Along with the reference in <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> this would make Harrag an elected High King of the Iron Islands. However, the section \"The Iron Islands: The Black Blood\" suggests that Harrag Hoare reigned as a hereditary <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"King of the Iron Islands\">King of the Iron Islands</a> some decades or centuries after <a href=\"/index.php/Hagon_Hoare\" title=\"Hagon Hoare\">Hagon Hoare</a> and the subsequent <a href=\"/index.php/Famine_Winter\" title=\"Famine Winter\">Famine Winter</a>, while still retaining the reference to his conflicts with Theon Stark.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_black_blood.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_black_blood.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> This is likely an error, as it is further mentioned in the section \"The North: The Kings of Winter\" that <a href=\"/index.php/Loron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Loron Greyjoy\">Loron Greyjoy</a>, another elected High King, reigned after Harrag Hoare.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Harrag_Hoare&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_1\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 1\">Chapter 1</a>, The Prophet.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_north:_the_kings_of_winter.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\">2.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The North: The Kings of Winter.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_black_blood.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_black_blood.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_black_blood.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Iron Islands: The Bl